[crlf.txt](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/files/7588894/crlf.txt)
[lf.txt](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/files/7588895/lf.txt)

Both are created in VS Code and one is just saved with CRLF endings and the other one with LF endings:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13891066/143046452-90bbbe67-0b06-4dd7-89ce-c3f3f792f8ad.png)

Change paths to yours in `_lfFilePath` and `_crlfFilePath` variables, run it.

If you place cursor at the end of the line, in the LF part is everything ok
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13891066/143046717-ecd74467-d90f-4f50-a3f3-19137fb1f173.png)

But in the CRLF part is this invisible `\r` char:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13891066/143046954-93929c1f-c9cd-419e-b95c-260ff7067e22.png)

I have also noticed that when you copy / paste it, Windows (presumably?) automatically converts LF to CRLF, so this actually happens even if you try to copy / paste LF text. But by directly comparing those two files it's clearer.

I was create the flutter application to format the date time and the text was rendered incorrectly. The text formatted correctly but it rendered wrongly. 

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Run the sample with below code
2. Set the locale as 'en' and change the directionality text direction as rtl(formatted texts are 06 PM, PM 06 but rendered PM 06, PM 06)
3. See both the different formatted text(english) rendered like same.
4. again change the locale as 'he' and change the directionality text direction as ltr
5. See both the different formatted text(hebrew) rendered like same.

<details>
<summary>code sample</summary>

```dart
void main() {
  return runApp(LocalizationSupport());
}

class LocalizationSupport extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      localizationsDelegates: [
        GlobalMaterialLocalizations.delegate,
        GlobalWidgetsLocalizations.delegate,
      ],
      supportedLocales: [
        const Locale('en'),
        const Locale('zh'),
        const Locale('ru'),
        const Locale('fr', 'BE'),
        const Locale('fr', 'CA'),
        const Locale('ja'),
        const Locale('de'),
        const Locale('hi'),
        const Locale('ar'),
        const Locale('he'),
      ],
      locale: const Locale('en'),
      debugShowCheckedModeBanner: false,
      home: StringLocale(),
    );
  }
}
class StringLocale extends StatefulWidget {
  @override
  State<StatefulWidget> createState() => StringLocaleState();
}
class StringLocaleState extends State<StringLocale> {
  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
  }

  late String _locale;
  @override
  void didChangeDependencies() {
    _locale = Localizations.localeOf(context).toString();
    super.didChangeDependencies();
  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    String data = DateFormat('hh a', _locale)
        .format(DateTime.now())
        .toString();
    print(data);

    String data1 = DateFormat('a hh', _locale)
        .format(DateTime.now())
        .toString();
    print(data1);

    if(data == data1){
      print('Same');
    }

    return Scaffold(
      body:
      Directionality(textDirection: TextDirection.rtl,
          child: SafeArea(child: Column(
        children: <Widget>[
          Expanded(
            child: Container(
          alignment: Alignment.center,
              height: double.infinity,
              width: double.infinity,
              child: Text(data),
      )
            ),Expanded(
              child: Container(
                alignment: Alignment.center,
                height: double.infinity,
                width: double.infinity,
                child: Text(data1),
              )
          )
      ]
          ),
      ),
    ));
  }
}

```
